# Model config: Qwen3-Coder-Next (UD-Q5_K_M, sharded GGUF) -- model-intrinsic only.
#
# 80B MoE, ~3B active (512 experts, 10 used). The Q5_K_M weights total ~56 GiB
# across three shards; point -m at the FIRST shard and llama.cpp loads the rest.
#
# This file holds ONLY what is intrinsic to the model (weight path + sampling).
# How it fits a given card -- CPU-MoE offload, context, KV quant -- is GPU-specific
# and lives in profiles/<machine>/qwen3-coder-next.env:
#   - profiles/strixhalo/qwen3-coder-next.env : N_CPU_MOE offload for unified memory.
#   - profiles/r9700-dual/qwen3-coder-next.env: all-VRAM split, no offload.
#
#   - Qwen3-Coder sampling: temp 0.7, top-p 0.8, top-k 20, repeat-penalty 1.05.

: "${MODEL:=Qwen3-Coder-Next/UD-Q5_K_M/Qwen3-Coder-Next-UD-Q5_K_M-00001-of-00003.gguf}"

LLAMA_ARGS+=(--temp 0.7 --top-p 0.8 --top-k 20 --repeat-penalty 1.05)
